I13(A) that each aggregator ensure within a reasonable time that each of its telephones presubscribed to a provider of operator services allows the consumer to obtain access to the provider of operator services desired by the consumer through the use of an equal access code; or

I13(B) that all providers of operator services, within a reasonable time, make available to their customers a ``950'' or ``800'' access code number for use in making operator services calls from anywhere in the United States; or

I13(C) that the requirements described under both subparagraphs (A) and (B) apply.

