I13(B) announce that its rates are available on request at the beginning of each call.

I79(3) Proceeding required

I18(A) In general

I13Within 60 days after October 17, 1990, the Commission shall initiate a proceeding to determine whether the regulatory objectives specified in subsection (d)(1)(A) and (B) of this section are being achieved. The proceeding shall_

I14(i) monitor operator service rates;

I14(ii) determine the extent to which offerings made by providers of operator services are improvements, in terms of service quality, price, innovation, and other factors, over those available before the entry of new providers of operator services into the market;

I14(iii) report on (in the aggregate and by individual provider) operator service rates, incidence of service complaints, and service offerings;

I14(iv) consider the effect that commissions and surcharges, billing and validation costs, and other costs of doing business have on the overall rates charged to consumers; and

