I89. Electronic publishing by Bell operating companies

I19(a) Limitations

I11No Bell operating company or any affiliate may engage in the provision of electronic publishing that is disseminated by means of such Bell operating company's or any of its affiliates' basic telephone service, except that nothing in this section shall prohibit a separated affiliate or electronic publishing joint venture operated in accordance with this section from engaging in the provision of electronic publishing.

I19(b) Separated affiliate or electronic publishing joint venture requirements

