I89. Judicial proceedings

I19(a) Actions to review determinations by franchising authorities

I11Any cable operator adversely affected by any final determination made by a franchising authority under section 541(a)(1), 545 or 546 of this title may commence an action within 120 days after receiving notice of such determination, which may be brought in_

I12(1) the district court of the United States for any judicial district in which the cable system is located; or

I12(2) in any State court of general jurisdiction having jurisdiction over the parties.

I19(b) Available relief

