I12(1) defining geographic coverage areas for public safety answering points;

I12(2) defining network diversity requirements for delivery of IP-enabled 9ÿ091ÿ091 and enhanced 9ÿ091ÿ091 calls;

I12(3) call-handling in the event of call overflow or network outages;

I12(4) public safety answering point certification and testing requirements;

I12(5) validation procedures for inputting and updating location information in relevant databases; and

I12(6) the format for delivering address information to public safety answering points.

I19(i) Rule of construction

I11Nothing in the New and Emerging Technologies 911 Improvement Act of 2008 shall be construed as altering, delaying, or otherwise limiting the ability of the Commission to enforce the Federal actions taken or rules adopted obligating an IP-enabled voice service provider to provide 9ÿ091ÿ091 or enhanced 9ÿ091ÿ091 service as of the date of enactment of the New and Emerging Technologies 911 Improvement Act of 2008.

