I89. Spectrum Relocation Fund

I19(a) Establishment of Spectrum Relocation Fund

I11There is established on the books of the Treasury a separate fund to be known as the ``Spectrum Relocation Fund'' (in this section referred to as the ``Fund''), which shall be administered by the Office of Management and Budget (in this section referred to as ``OMB''), in consultation with the NTIA.

I19(b) Crediting of receipts

I11The Fund shall be credited with the amounts specified in section 309(j)(8)(D) of this title.

I19(c) Use of funds

I11The amounts in the Fund from auctions of eligible frequencies are authorized to be used to pay relocation or sharing costs of an eligible Federal entity incurring such costs with respect to relocation from or sharing of those frequencies.

I19(d) Fund availability

I79(1) Appropriation

I12There are hereby appropriated from the Fund such sums as are required to pay the relocation or sharing costs specified in subsection (c) of this section.

I79(2) Transfer conditions

I12None of the funds provided under this subsection may be transferred to any eligible Federal entity_

I13(A) unless the eligible Federal entity has submitted a transition plan to the NTIA as required by paragraph (1) of section 923(h) of this title, the Technical Panel has found such plan sufficient under paragraph (4) of such section, and the NTIA has made available such plan on its website as required by paragraph (5) of such section;

I13(B) unless the Director of OMB has determined, in consultation with the NTIA, the appropriateness of such costs and the timeline for relocation or sharing; and

I13(C) until 30 days after the Director of OMB has submitted to the Committees on Appropriations and Energy and Commerce of the House of Representatives for approval, to the Committees on Appropriations and Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate for approval, and to the Comptroller General a detailed plan describing specifically how the sums transferred from the Fund will be used to pay relocation or sharing costs in accordance with such subsection and the timeline for such relocation or sharing.

