I17Unless disapproved within 30 days, the amounts in the Fund shall be available immediately. If the plan is disapproved, the Director may resubmit a revised plan.

I79(3) Transfers for pre-auction costs

I18(A) In general

I13Subject to subparagraph (B), the Director of OMB may transfer to an eligible Federal entity, at any time (including prior to a scheduled auction), such sums as may be available in the Fund to pay relocation or sharing costs related to pre-auction estimates or research, as such costs are described in section 923(g)(3)(A)(iii) of this title.

I18(B) Notification

I13No funds may be transferred pursuant to subparagraph (A) unless_

I14(i) the notification provided under paragraph (2)(C) includes a certification from the Director of OMB that_

I16(I) funds transferred before an auction will likely allow for timely implementation of relocation or sharing, thereby increasing net expected auction proceeds by an amount not less than the time value of the amount of funds transferred; and

I16(II) the auction is intended to occur not later than 5 years after transfer of funds; and

Q04

I14(ii) the transition plan submitted by the eligible Federal entity under section 923(h)(1) of this title provides_

I16(I) to the fullest extent possible, for sharing and coordination of eligible frequencies with non-Federal users, including reasonable accommodation by the eligible Federal entity for the use of eligible frequencies by non-Federal users during the period that the entity is relocating its spectrum uses (in this clause referred to as the ``transition period'');

